cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a new framework for learning flexible point process models using reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on modeling social goods, such as healthcare, smart city, and information networks, which often produce ordered event data in continuous time. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also uses recurrent neural networks to parameterize the policy, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with social goods, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for learning point process models, which could also place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
